Atherosclerotic occlusive disease of the superior mesenteric artery: late results of reconstructive surgery. Between 1975 and 1988, 103 patients underwent reconstruction of the superior mesenteric artery for atherosclerotic occlusive disease. Patients undergoing revascularization with associated mesenteric infarction were excluded. There were 89 men and 14 women whose mean age was 57.2 years. Six patients were operated on emergently for impending mesenteric infarction six patients underwent revascularization after intestinal resection for ischemic lesions